            "description": "Roundcube is an international product for larger insurance companies. With Roundcube they can easily manage and configure their claims process.\n\nWhen I started at the project, the project was ongoing for over a year and was struggled in meeting the deadlines. By introducing test automation and focusing on the development life cycle, we were as a team able to meet the deadlines and the proper quality. \n\nWe used unit tests, Selenium and SoapUI for our test automation. For the DLC we used Ant, Jenkins and TFS. We focused on the functionality that really added value within the Scrum sprints of two weeks. We worked in a distributed Scrum team with colleagues in Hyderabad, India. ",
